<paper id="1551246917"><title>Combining Model Checking and Deduction for I/O-Automata</title><year>1995</year><authors><author org="Technische Universität München;" id="2298578953">Olaf Müller</author><author org="Technische Universität München;" id="42605653">Tobias Nipkow</author></authors><n_citation>47</n_citation><doc_type>Conference</doc_type><references><reference>1498539321</reference><reference>1499481996</reference><reference>1514983780</reference><reference>1543208154</reference><reference>1796678419</reference><reference>1978358700</reference><reference>1991956281</reference><reference>2000302396</reference><reference>2012001501</reference><reference>2088184419</reference><reference>2114092850</reference><reference>2123160677</reference></references><venue id="1159071770" type="C">Tools and Algorithms for Construction and Analysis of Systems</venue><doi>10.1007/3-540-60630-0_1</doi><keywords><keyword weight="0.44563">Discrete mathematics</keyword><keyword weight="0.60054">Abstraction model checking</keyword><keyword weight="0.57619">Model checking</keyword><keyword weight="0.54511">Alternating bit protocol</keyword><keyword weight="0.43841">Computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.47321">Automaton</keyword><keyword weight="0.55911">Automated theorem proving</keyword><keyword weight="0.58992">Automated proof checking</keyword><keyword weight="0.45846">Algorithm</keyword><keyword weight="0.48546">Input/output</keyword><keyword weight="0.45513">Theoretical computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.54636">Proof assistant</keyword></keywords><publisher>Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg</publisher><abstract>We propose a combination of model checking and interactive theorem proving where the theorem prover is used to represent finite and infinite state systems, reason about them compositionally and reduce them to small finite systems by verified abstractions. As an example we verify a version of the Alternating Bit Protocol with unbounded lossy and duplicating channels: the channels are abstracted by interactive proof and the resulting finite state system is model checked.</abstract></paper>